# Smart Grid Digital Twin — Full 5-Layer Architecture Overhaul

## Overview

Transform the existing microgrid simulation into a comprehensive, industry-grade **5-Layer City Power Grid Digital Twin**, implementing every entity, attribute, and physics model from the blueprint. The current app has ~5 nodes (substation, solar, 3 residential, optional factory/capacitor). The new system will have **14+ distinct entities** across 5 hierarchical layers with real-time telemetry streaming for every asset.

---

## Architecture Summary

### Current State
- 1 substation, 1 solar farm, 3 residential zones, optional factory/capacitor
- Simple per-unit voltage drop model
- Basic fault detection (only factory-triggered)
- 5 power lines

### Target State (5-Layer City Grid)
- **Layer 1**: Coal Power Plant + Solar Farm (Bulk Generation) → ~3 entities
- **Layer 2**: Primary HV Substation + Heavy Industry Complex (City Gateway) → ~3 entities  
- **Layer 3**: Zone Distribution Substations + Automated RMUs (Urban Veins) → ~5 entities
- **Layer 4**: Distribution Transformers + Smart Meters (Intelligent Edge) → ~4 entities
- **Layer 5**: Data pipeline with per-entity telemetry streams
- ~15 power lines with voltage-appropriate simulation

---

