## Spatial Layout

The 3D scene will use a **radial city layout**:

```
                    [Coal Plant] (-30, 0, -35)
                         |
                    [Solar Farm] (-18, 0, -30)
                         |
            [HV Primary Substation] (0, 0, -20)   [Gas Stabilizer] (20, 0, -30)
           /           |          \
    [Zone Sub West]  [Zone Sub North]  [Zone Sub East]
    (-20, 0, 0)       (0, 0, 5)        (20, 0, 0)
          |               |                |
    [Heavy Industry]  [RMU North]      [RMU East]
    (-22, 0, 10)      (0, 0, 15)       (20, 0, 12)
                          |                |
                    [Dist. Trans α]    [Dist. Trans β]
                    (-8, 0, 22)        (12, 0, 22)
                          |                |
                  [Smart Meter Res]  [Smart Meter Hospital]
                  (-8, 0, 30)        (12, 0, 30)
```

---

## Key Design Decisions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Self-Healing Ring**: The North↔East ring tie is the core "smart grid" feature. When RMU North detects a fault current, it isolates the faulted segment, and the ring tie path automatically re-energizes the load from East. This is the key differentiator from the old simple topology.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **GLB Mapping**: Per user instructions: `hv_substation.glb` = compound substation facility (Layer 2 & 3). `substation.glb` = single distribution transformer (Layer 4). `ring_main_unit.glb` = RMU street-level switch. `coal plant.glb` = coal plant. `gas_stabilizer_plant.glb` = gas plant.

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking Change**: The old node IDs (`substation`, `residential1-3`) are completely replaced. The AI Advisor prompts will need updating to reference new entity IDs. Old `resetGrid` will point to new topology.

